narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely; take it! Its really cool material which is very applicable if you like neuroscience!

First half: medium-level lectures on mainly auditory and visual processing. Second half: students presenting on current research on topics of synaesthesia. Pros: small lecture without too much work and some interesting topics. Cons: I don't remember most of the material we covered and I've also lost all my senses. It's really kind of unfortunate.
This class covers a wide variety of ways in which humans process sensory information. Overall, the material is interesting, especially when you research topics for your presentation or paper.
A good course to take if you're interested in issues surrounding both physiological and higher level sensory processing. If that's you, then it's hard to avoid a course like this.
